attributes.Long form description: The student begins by unscrewing the screws that join one of the bases of the furniture to the legs, then removes the first base, then he is unscrews the rest of the screws that join the legs. Finally, the student disassembles the base and the legs of the furniture, thus ending the task.

attributes.Transcription: So your task is to disassemble the furniture.

attributes.Action sentence: The student loosens all the hex socket heads attached to the upper tray.

attributes.Transcription: Please start by loosening all screws a little bit, but not removing them completely.

attributes.Action sentence: The student loosens all the hex socket heads attached to the lower tray.
The student disassembles the upper tray.

attributes.Transcription: Please start by removing the top part of the table.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the first leg.
The student disassembles the second leg.
The student disassembles the third leg.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: Screw is too tight to unscrew.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the fourth leg along with the lower tray.

attributes.Transcription: Your task is over and you can stop recording.
